## Testing Instructions for Judges

### 1. Prerequisites: Chrome Canary & AI Flags

**This extension requires Google Chrome Canary and specific experimental flags to be enabled.**

-   First, download and install [Google Chrome Canary](https://www.google.com/chrome/canary/).
-   Next, navigate to the flags page by typing this in the address bar:
    ```
    chrome://flags
    ```
-   Enable the following two flags:
    -   `#optimization-guide-on-device-model`
    -   `#prompt-api-for-gemini-nano`
-   After enabling the flags, **relaunch** your browser.

_Note: The first time you launch, Chrome will download the Gemini Nano model in the background. This may take a few minutes._

### 2. Loading the Extension

1.  **Download the Code:**
    -   Visit the GitHub repository: [ketarora/Shop_smart](https://github.com/ketarora/Shop_smart)
    -   Click the green **Code** button and select **Download ZIP**.
    -   Unzip the downloaded file on your computer.

2.  **Install the Extension:**
    -   Open Chrome Canary and navigate to `chrome://extensions`.
    -   Enable **Developer mode** using the toggle in the top-right corner.
    -   Click the **Load unpacked** button.
    -   Select the unzipped `Shop_smart-main` folder.
    -   The **ShopSmart AI** extension will now appear in your list and in the toolbar.

### 3. How to Test

1.  Navigate to a product page on a supported e-commerce site, such as:
    -   [Amazon.in](https://www.amazon.in)
    -   [Amazon.com](https://www.amazon.com)
    -   [Flipkart.com](https://www.flipkart.com)

2.  Once the page loads, the **ShopSmart AI badge** will appear in the bottom-right corner, showing the initial analysis (default is EcoScore).

3.  Click the **ShopSmart AI icon** in your Chrome toolbar to open the popup.

4.  Inside the popup, use the toggle buttons to switch between **üåø EcoScore** and **üõ°Ô∏è Trust Score** modes. The on-page badge and the popup details will update accordingly.

5.  Click the **View Full Analysis** button to open the side panel and see a detailed breakdown of the selected score.

The relationship between the analysis modes \\(M_{eco}, M_{trust}\\) and the final score \\(S\\) can be thought of as:
$$
S = f(\text{ProductData}, M_{\text{selected}})
$$
where \\(f\\) is the AI analysis function.
